\begin_layout Theorem
For calorically ideal gases, the states on the two sides of a shock are
 related by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
u_{2}-u_{1}=v_{2}-v_{2}=\frac{p_{2}-p_{1}}{-\sqrt{\rho_{1}P}}\cdot\begin{cases}
+1 & m>0\\
-1 & m<0
\end{cases}\label{eq:AbsoluteSpeedChangeVsPressureChangeForShock}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $P:=\frac{\gamma+1}{2}p_{2}+\frac{\gamma-1}{2}p_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $m:=v_{1}\rho_{1}=v_{2}\rho_{2}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Treat 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{1},u_{1},p_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{2}$
\end_inset

 as known variables, 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:JumpConditionEuler1d"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 becomes a system of 3 independent algebraic equations for 3 unknowns 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{2},u_{2}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $v$
\end_inset

.
 Represent 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{2}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $v$
\end_inset

 in terms of 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{2}$
\end_inset

 (and the knowns), we will obtain an equation for 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{2}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Multiply the 1st line of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:JumpConditionEuler1d"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{2}$
\end_inset

 and subtract it from the 2nd line, we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
(u_{1}-v)(u_{1}-u_{2})\rho_{1}=p_{2}-p_{1}
\]

\end_inset

from which
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v=u_{1}+\frac{p_{2}-p_{1}}{u_{2}-u_{1}}\frac{1}{\rho_{1}}
\]

\end_inset

Substitute it back into the 1st line of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:JumpConditionEuler1d"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and solve for 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{2}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\rho_{2}=\frac{u_{1}-v}{u_{2}-v}\rho_{1}=\frac{p_{2}-p_{1}}{p_{2}-p_{1}-(u_{2}-u_{1})^{2}\rho_{1}}\rho_{1}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Substitute these expressions for 
\begin_inset Formula $v$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{2}$
\end_inset

 into the 3rd line of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:JumpConditionEuler1d"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, we obtain a quadratic equation for 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{2}$
\end_inset

